{!</table>!}

= Volkisch Parties [+ volkisch_parties +]%

Volkisch Parties believe in the idea of "Blood and Soil"- A fundamental tie between the land and the people that live on it. Differing from conservative parties who focus on the past of our fathers or grandfathers, Volkisch groups call back to an even more ancient tradition that requires a revolution of societal norms to be brought back. 

In current Germany politics, antisemite candidates in rural constituencies are the only outright Volkisch candidates that have reached success. The DSP and the DVP fight over the fate of the Volkisch movement in intellectual circles and influence said candidates, but have traditionally failed to secure urban seats or rural constituencies by just as anti-semitic DKP candidates. Some of the more extreme candidates in the DVLP adopt a stance that can be said to be Volkisch in nature, but cannot claim to be as dedicated as DSP or DVP candidates traditionally are.

